00:57:42,150 --> 00:57:45,520
Ask...Yes, I know.

734
00:57:45,520 --> 00:57:49,930
I...see him now.

735
00:57:49,930 --> 00:57:53,770
The uniform. A chauffeur.

736
00:57:53,770 --> 00:57:56,470
What? Henry, I need words.

737
00:57:56,470 --> 00:57:58,470
Who? The what?

738
00:57:58,470 --> 00:58:01,840
The Rainbird chauffeur?

739
00:58:01,840 --> 00:58:05,540
Good heavens. Old Michael O'Keefe, our chauffeur.

740
00:58:05,540 --> 00:58:08,410
Where is Michael going?

741
00:58:08,410 --> 00:58:12,480
Henry, ask him where he's taking Harriet's baby.

742
00:58:12,480 --> 00:58:15,290
Oh, more pictures are coming in too fast.

743
00:58:15,290 --> 00:58:18,060
I can hardly make them out.

744
00:58:18,060 --> 00:58:21,430
Henry, a graveyard, a headstone?

745
00:58:21,430 --> 00:58:23,860
I don't like this, Henry.

746
00:58:23,860 --> 00:58:26,870
A shoe. Bridge.

747
00:58:26,870 --> 00:58:31,100
A shoe bridge? Oh, don't do this to me, Henry.

748
00:58:31,100 --> 00:58:34,770
- Speak to the chauffeur.  - Oh, God, something's burning.

749
00:58:34,770 --> 00:58:38,780
The house. Quick, Henry. The house is on fire.

750
00:58:38,780 --> 00:58:41,180
Take me away from here.

751
00:58:41,180 --> 00:58:43,210
I don't want to see this.

752
00:58:43,210 --> 00:58:46,890
I can't bear the sound of their awful screaming.

753
00:58:46,890 --> 00:58:50,120
Go back to the chauffeur, Henry. Get Michael into our presence.

754
00:58:50,120 --> 00:58:52,220
Miss Rainbird remembers him.

755
00:58:52,220 --> 00:58:55,390
Yes, I remember.

756
00:58:55,390 --> 00:58:58,130
Madame Blanche, listen to me.

757
00:58:58,130 --> 00:59:02,030
Can you hear me?

758
00:59:02,030 --> 00:59:06,170
I've remembered something else that could be terribly important.

759
00:59:06,170 --> 00:59:09,610
Wait one minute, Henry. Before you go,

760
00:59:09,610 --> 00:59:13,910
Miss Rainbird deserves some kind of assurance about Harriet's child.

761
00:59:13,910 --> 00:59:16,680
He's a man by now,

762
00:59:16,680 --> 00:59:20,150
and we have to know, is he happy, Henry?

763
00:59:20,150 --> 00:59:23,880
Is he alive and well and happy?

764
00:59:25,290 --> 00:59:27,590
If you can't, you can't.

765
00:59:27,590 --> 00:59:30,360
I certainly can't force you.

766
00:59:30,360 --> 00:59:34,500
Yes. Of course she'll understand.

767
00:59:34,500 --> 00:59:38,700
Until next time, then. Good-bye.

768
00:59:38,700 --> 00:59:41,140
Good-bye, my love.

769
00:59:44,240 --> 00:59:47,270
- What happened?  - Don't you remember?

770
00:59:48,680 --> 00:59:52,550
- Not a blessed thing.  - Oh, it doesn't matter now.

771
00:59:52,550 --> 00:59:55,090
Listen, listen, Madame Blanche.

772
00:59:55,090 --> 00:59:59,790
Your Henry jogged my memory of something I'd completely forgotten.

773
00:59:59,790 --> 01:00:03,930
When our poor old chauffeur, Mike, realized he was dying,

774
01:00:03,930 --> 01:00:08,130
he wrote to me and said there was one person on earth...

775
01:00:08,130 --> 01:00:11,040
who had promised that he'd make it his business...

776
01:00:11,040 --> 01:00:15,540
to know where Harriet's son was as long as he lived.

777
01:00:15,540 --> 01:00:20,810
It was the parson who baptized the newborn baby.

778
01:00:20,810 --> 01:00:24,080
And there's an additional thing I can tell you.

779
01:00:24,650 --> 01:00:28,250
Don't tell me. Let me guess.

780
01:00:28,250 --> 01:00:31,790
- Five hundred.  - Not a penny. Not even a hundred for expenses.

781
01:00:31,790 --> 01:00:33,790
It's all or nothing, George,

782
01:00:33,790 --> 01:00:36,330
until I can produce his name and his present address.

783
01:00:36,330 --> 01:00:40,530
- Jesus, Blanche.  - However, she gave me a marvelous clue.

784
01:00:40,530 --> 01:00:43,500
- Here we go again.  - No, here you go again...

785
01:00:43,500 --> 01:00:46,540
to the man who might tell you if Shoebridge is dead or alive.

786
01:00:46,540 --> 01:00:50,680
- Who's that?  - Bishop Wood at St. Anselm's Cathedral.

787
01:00:50,680 --> 01:00:53,610
- Holy Christ, Blanche.  - No, George, not him.

788
01:00:53,610 --> 01:00:56,250
Bishop Wood at St. Anselm's Cathedral.

789
01:00:56,250 --> 01:01:00,680
He was a parson once and he baptized the Shoebridge baby.

790
01:01:48,500 --> 01:01:50,930
Excuse me.

791
01:01:54,270 --> 01:01:56,310
Sorry.

792
01:01:56,310 --> 01:02:00,710
Do you know how I could, uh, make a date to see Bishop Wood?

793
01:02:00,710 --> 01:02:05,780
If you want to make the appointment today, you'll have to make it through the chaplain.

794
01:02:05,780 --> 01:02:08,350
Which one is the chaplain?

795
01:02:08,350 --> 01:02:11,620
When the service is over, I'll show you where to go.

796
01:02:34,410 --> 01:02:38,640
Oh, dear.

797
01:03:19,750 --> 01:03:22,520
You know he's moving. You sure you gave him enough?

798
01:03:22,520 --> 01:03:26,260
Just the usual dose. He looks so harmless.

799
01:03:26,260 --> 01:03:29,430
When I was a little kid living in that village,

800
01:03:29,430 --> 01:03:32,300
he always made me feel like I was something evil.

801
01:03:32,300 --> 01:03:36,230
- And look at me now.  - I feel years younger.

802
01:03:36,230 --> 01:03:39,400
You know, one more like this one today, and we'll be naturally gray.

803
01:03:39,400 --> 01:03:43,740
It was an incredible job. I really think it's won'th more than a million.

804
01:03:43,740 --> 01:03:46,430
I'm sorry, darling, but I'm not going back...

805
01:03:46,440 --> 01:03:49,250
and rewrite my ransom note that I left in my prayer book.

806
01:03:49,250 --> 01:03:52,280
You'll have to be a good sport and settle for a million.

807
01:03:52,280 --> 01:03:54,990
You were beautiful, Fran. Just beautiful.

808
01:03:54,990 --> 01:03:58,790
- I was scared.  - I told you it'd be all right, didn't I?

809
01:03:58,790 --> 01:04:01,560
People in church are inibited.

810
01:04:01,560 --> 01:04:06,100
They don't jump up and run around and make a lot of noise. They're all too religiously polite.

811
01:04:06,100 --> 01:04:10,970
Shall we go on congratulating ourselves, or would you like to talk about him now?

812
01:04:10,970 --> 01:04:13,700
- Who?  - "Who."

813
01:04:13,700 --> 01:04:16,410
The man with the pipe.

814
01:04:16,410 --> 01:04:20,680
- So you saw him there, huh?  - Larger than life.

815
01:04:20,680 --> 01:04:22,680
Larger than death, you mean.

816
01:04:22,680 --> 01:04:24,980
There's no doubt about who he's after now.

817
01:04:24,980 --> 01:04:27,280
What were you planning to do about him, dear,

818
01:04:27,280 --> 01:04:29,520
besides just not telling me?

819
01:04:29,520 --> 01:04:33,060
I'm not planning to do anything about him.

820
01:04:33,060 --> 01:04:36,630
Joe Maloney's been itching for that job. He's got it.

821
01:04:36,630 --> 01:04:40,300
I'll phone him as soon as we put our guest in his quarters.

822
01:04:40,300 --> 01:04:43,730
I was right about that silly cab driver.

823
01:04:43,730 --> 01:04:46,340
For once in my life I hate being right.

824
01:04:46,340 --> 01:04:51,210
Well, how in the hell could he have known we were going to be there... when you and I are the only two people in the world who knew that?

825
01:04:51,210 --> 01:04:53,210
I've got a thought.

826
01:04:53,210 --> 01:04:55,880
- It's a dumb one.  - Say it.

827
01:04:55,880 --> 01:04:58,010
Do you believe in E.S.P.?

828
01:04:58,010 --> 01:05:01,420
Extra sensory perception, all that psychic phenomena?

829
01:05:01,420 --> 01:05:04,320
What do you mean? Madame What's-her-name?

830
01:05:04,320 --> 01:05:06,820
Blanche Tyler.

831
01:05:06,820 --> 01:05:09,090
Jesus.

832
01:05:09,090 --> 01:05:14,500
You and I know that that's off the wall, but, uh, can we afford to be wrong?

833
01:05:15,900 --> 01:05:20,040
I'm afraid our two quarrelsome lovers are going to have to share a fatal accident.

834
01:05:20,040 --> 01:05:22,470
Oh, my God.

835
01:05:23,410 --> 01:05:25,780
But Maloney wouldn't be willing to do that, would he?

836
01:05:25,780 --> 01:05:29,550
Of course he'd be willing. Gladly.

837
01:05:29,550 --> 01:05:33,550
He'd believe he was protecting himself and his old buddy.

838
01:05:33,550 --> 01:05:36,550
I don't want to know about it. Okay?

839
01:05:36,550 --> 01:05:39,760
- Promise me, Arthur.  - Come on, now, dear.

840
01:05:39,760 --> 01:05:43,130
That's what's so exciting about all of this.

841
01:05:43,130 --> 01:05:47,190
We move as one. Everything together. Nothing held back.

842
01:06:18,130 --> 01:06:22,130
It was gross negligence, losing him that way. He was all we had.

843
01:06:22,130 --> 01:06:25,070
I didn't lose him. He was kidnapped.

844
01:06:27,970 --> 01:06:30,740
Why would anyone want to do that to a bishop?

845
01:06:30,740 --> 01:06:34,370
For the ransom, dummy. It's a million dollars.

846
01:06:38,280 --> 01:06:41,920
I can't get over it. You know, I was right there.

847
01:06:41,920 --> 01:06:46,650
Tsk. Oh, forget about the million. What about out 10,000?

848
01:06:48,830 --> 01:06:51,590
We've got nowhere to go now, Lumley.

849
01:06:52,200 --> 01:06:55,400
What am I gonna tell Miss Rainbird?

850
01:06:55,400 --> 01:07:00,040
I suppose Henry and I are going to have to exhaust ourselves again doing your work for you.

851
01:07:00,040 --> 01:07:03,560
What d'ya mean, my work? My work is driving a goddamn cab, for Christ's sake.

852
01:07:03,570 --> 01:07:07,040
And startir right this minute, that's exact...

853
01:07:07,040 --> 01:07:10,410
- That's exact what? Go ahead.  - Answer the telephone.

854
01:07:15,120 --> 01:07:18,590
Hello? Who?

855
01:07:18,590 --> 01:07:20,720
Mr. Maloney?

856
01:07:20,720 --> 01:07:23,930
Barlow Creek? Go ahead.

857
01:07:23,930 --> 01:07:27,060
Hello.

858
01:07:27,060 --> 01:07:29,700
Can you speak a little louder, Mr. Maloney?

859
01:07:29,700 --> 01:07:34,240
I said I traced you through the license plates on that car your lawyer friend was driving.

860
01:07:34,240 --> 01:07:37,340
I figured if you was still lookir for some dope on Eddie Shoebridge,

861
01:07:37,340 --> 01:07:39,840
- I might have somethir for you.  - Oh.

862
01:07:39,840 --> 01:07:42,610
How come you changed your mind, Mr. Maloney?

863
01:07:42,610 --> 01:07:46,820
I didn't say nothir to your man 'cause I felt it was none of my business and none of his,

864
01:07:46,820 --> 01:07:49,320
but I been thinkir about it and how I could use the bread.

865
01:07:49,320 --> 01:07:52,020
So for a little consideration, I'm willing to lead you to someone...

866
01:07:52,020 --> 01:07:54,160
who knows Eddie Shoebridge's wife.

867
01:07:54,160 --> 01:07:57,130
It'll cost you a grand.

868
01:07:57,130 --> 01:07:59,860
Oh, don't be silly, Mr. Maloney.

869
01:07:59,860 --> 01:08:02,070
I have my lawyer right here beside me,

870
01:08:02,070 --> 01:08:06,830
and he says he'll give you $100 provided it leads to something. Make it two.

871
01:08:08,840 --> 01:08:12,410
Oh... All right. It's a deal.

872
01:08:12,410 --> 01:08:14,940
- Where do we meet?  - You and that lawyer friend of yours,

873
01:08:14,940 --> 01:08:17,750
you drive up and meet me at Abe and Mabel's in two hours.

874
01:08:17,750 --> 01:08:22,590
- Abe and Mabel's?  - It's a cafe up the road to Mt. Sherman,

875
01:08:22,590 --> 01:08:26,480
about five miles off Route 22. You know where it is?

876
01:08:26,490 --> 01:08:29,990
Yeah. Why so far away? Can't we meet somewhere more convenient?

877
01:08:29,990 --> 01:08:33,660
This party I'm gonna take you to happens to be up in that area.

878
01:08:33,660 --> 01:08:37,830
I see. Mr. Maloney, are you admitting Edward Shoebridge is still alive?

879
01:08:37,830 --> 01:08:41,200
I ain't sayir a thing till I see the color of your money, in two hours.

880
01:08:44,640 --> 01:08:46,780
- What d'ya think?  - Smells fishy to me.

881
01:08:46,780 --> 01:08:48,780
I know.

882
01:08:48,780 --> 01:08:52,480
But even fish smells good when you're starving to death.

883
01:08:52,480 --> 01:08:55,420
What have we got to lose? He's the only clue left.

884
01:08:56,350 --> 01:08:59,060
You got $200 on you?

885
01:08:59,060 --> 01:09:01,060
You know me better than that.

886
01:09:01,060 --> 01:09:05,230
Of course not. Fix me another one of these.

887
01:09:05,230 --> 01:09:09,630
You don't need another one. You already got one. We only got two hours to get there.

888
01:09:09,630 --> 01:09:12,800
- I'll eat it in the car.  - Come on.

889
01:09:12,800 --> 01:09:15,170
You're impossible.

890
01:10:48,230 --> 01:10:50,670
A couple of beers, please.

891
01:10:55,740 --> 01:10:58,760
He must be late.

892
01:11:21,300 --> 01:11:25,500
Thank you, dear.

893
01:11:35,780 --> 01:11:38,210
You kids sit over there.

894
01:11:45,590 --> 01:11:49,030
- How was Sunday school today?  - Noisy.

895
01:11:49,030 --> 01:11:51,790
- Five Cokes, please.  - We didn't make any noise.

896
01:11:51,790 --> 01:11:53,800
That's right. That's why you're here.

897
01:12:19,360 --> 01:12:21,590
Don't blame me.

898
01:12:21,590 --> 01:12:24,030
Did I say anything?

899
01:12:31,270 --> 01:12:34,000
- Hello. I'm sorry I'm late.  - I'll get you a chair.

900
01:12:34,000 --> 01:12:37,440
- That's all right. I'll sit over here.  - I'll join you.

901
01:12:45,350 --> 01:12:48,350
Look at that. Nice arrangement.

902
01:12:48,350 --> 01:12:51,480
Don't be obscene, George.

903
01:12:59,360 --> 01:13:01,400
Oh.

904
01:13:01,400 --> 01:13:03,400
Thank you, my dear.

905
01:13:08,370 --> 01:13:12,000
Just see that you keep you head screwed on straight, will you?

906
01:13:23,650 --> 01:13:26,090
He's not coming.

907
01:14:41,260 --> 01:14:43,700
Well, that's the end of that.

908
01:14:55,750 --> 01:14:58,180
George, what's the big hurry?

909
01:15:04,150 --> 01:15:06,360
Just slow down a little, will ya, please?

910
01:15:08,360 --> 01:15:11,330
I told you not to drive so fast, George!

911
01:15:11,330 --> 01:15:14,420
I don't know what's wrong. The accelerator seems to be sticking.

912
01:15:16,000 --> 01:15:19,170
George, for God's sake, slow up, will ya?

913
01:15:19,170 --> 01:15:21,240
I can't.

914
01:15:21,240 --> 01:15:23,670
My hamburger's coming up.

915
01:15:23,670 --> 01:15:26,610
The accelerator... is stuck.

916
01:15:26,610 --> 01:15:29,080
Use the brakes!

917
01:15:31,310 --> 01:15:33,750
- They don't work.  - What?

918
01:15:34,620 --> 01:15:38,310
- The brakes don't work.  - What do you mean?

919
01:15:42,560 --> 01:15:45,930
- George!  - Come on, woman. Don't grab me, for God's sake!

920
01:15:45,930 --> 01:15:48,100
It's not me. It's the brakes don't work.

921
01:15:48,100 --> 01:15:51,900
I'm getting violently ill, George.

922
01:15:51,900 --> 01:15:55,740
- You're chokir me, Blanche, for Christ's sake!  - George!

923
01:15:55,740 --> 01:15:59,140
Do something!

924
01:16:05,480 --> 01:16:09,150
Grab the brake! Reach down and pull the hand brake.

925
01:16:09,150 --> 01:16:11,250
- Pull on it!  - I am pulling!

926
01:16:11,250 --> 01:16:13,420
Get your hands off the steering wheel. Pull on it!

927
01:16:13,420 --> 01:16:15,860
- I am pulling.  - Pull it.

928
01:16:17,660 --> 01:16:20,090
Come on.

929
01:16:21,160 --> 01:16:23,930
Get your hand off the goddamn wheel!

930
01:17:06,140 --> 01:17:09,630
I gotta get off this road.

931
01:17:12,550 --> 01:17:14,710
Blanche, just hang on.

932
01:18:28,820 --> 01:18:31,190
Wasrt that fun?

933
01:18:31,190 --> 01:18:34,530
- Damn you, George Lumley!  - What's the matter with you?

934
01:18:34,530 --> 01:18:37,300
- It was't me. It's Maloney.  - He was't driving!

935
01:18:37,300 --> 01:18:40,340
Of course, but he screwed up the car and broke the brakes.

936
01:18:40,340 --> 01:18:42,710
- Maloney?  - Yes.

937
01:18:42,710 --> 01:18:45,910
You think it's a coincidence, Blanche?

938
01:18:45,910 --> 01:18:48,340
Huh?

939
01:18:50,150 --> 01:18:54,080
Your car... is gonna be out of commission for a couple days.

940
01:18:54,080 --> 01:18:58,280
So let's go find us another way to get home.

941
01:18:59,460 --> 01:19:02,930
George. Are you all right?

942
01:19:02,930 --> 01:19:06,700
Mm-hmm. I think so. How about you?

943
01:19:06,700 --> 01:19:10,530
I'm okay. I'm sorry.

944
01:19:12,740 --> 01:19:16,940
- Do you really think Maloney wanted us dead?  - Mm-hmm.

945
01:19:16,940 --> 01:19:22,180
Why, in the name of God, would anyone want to do that to us?

946
01:19:22,180 --> 01:19:24,180
I don't know,

947
01:19:24,180 --> 01:19:28,220
but you can bet is has something to do with your mysterious friend, Eddie Shoebridge.

948
01:19:28,220 --> 01:19:30,990
Maloney's probably got him buried in his backyard.

949
01:19:30,990 --> 01:19:34,220
Doesrt want us to find out.

950
01:20:02,480 --> 01:20:04,920
That way.

951
01:20:41,990 --> 01:20:43,990
Hi there. Sorry I'm late.

952
01:20:43,990 --> 01:20:47,760
Congratulations on the nice job you did on our car, Maloney.

953
01:20:47,760 --> 01:20:50,970
What are you two doir standir in the middle of the road?

954
01:20:50,970 --> 01:20:54,040
You know perfectly well what we're doing on the road, Maloney.

955
01:20:54,040 --> 01:20:57,570
You must be Blanche Tyler. Pleased to meet ya. Where's your car?

956
01:20:57,570 --> 01:21:00,680
Let's just say it ain't in runnir order, you know what I mean?

957
01:21:00,680 --> 01:21:02,880
Hop in. I'll give ya a lift to the nearest station.

958
01:21:02,880 --> 01:21:06,310
No, thank you. We don't ride in hearses.

959
01:21:07,450 --> 01:21:09,450
You think I came up here for the fun of it?

960
01:21:09,450 --> 01:21:12,120
Then you want me to take you to this party that knows Eddie Shoebridge's wife.

961
01:21:12,120 --> 01:21:17,620
Why don't you just go ahead, uh, by yourself this time, Maloney. We'll skip it.

962
01:21:27,700 --> 01:21:30,140
He's all charm.

963
01:22:14,220 --> 01:22:16,690
Who's that?

964
01:22:16,690 --> 01:22:19,520
That's Maloney. He's after us.

965
01:22:19,520 --> 01:22:22,790
Come on.

966
01:22:31,270 --> 01:22:33,700
Hey, guys, let's get the hell outta here.

967
01:23:03,130 --> 01:23:05,600
We better get the police.

968
01:23:07,670 --> 01:23:10,100
And lose our $10,000?

969
01:23:37,500 --> 01:23:40,000
May I be of some help to you, madam?

970
01:23:40,000 --> 01:23:44,240
- I'd like to see some bracelets.  - Any particular kind?

971
01:23:44,240 --> 01:23:48,400
Do you have anything with turquoise, or perhaps pearls?

972
01:23:55,980 --> 01:23:58,920
- Anything wrong with our houseguest?  - He's fine.

973
01:23:58,920 --> 01:24:03,490
